msItem.title: Treatise on rondeaux, ballades, virelais, etc., f. 207r

supportDesc.extent: 263 leaves : 147 x 111 mm. bound to 154 x 109 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 263; [1-263], modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a Gothic cursive script by multiple hands.

decoDesc.decoNote: Decorated initials with penwork ornamentation throughout, most in red ink, some in red and ochre, with an especially elaborate example (f. 64v); musical diagrams in red, blue, and black ink (f. 215v, 216r).
Reused manuscript leaf pastedown, Inside front cover

binding.p: Contemporary pigskin over wooden boards, with clasp intact; many wormholes in binding.

origin.p: Written in Germany in 1437 (f. 58r) and subsequent years, in a variety of hands.
